Description: The temptation of Saint Antony [second version]; the saint is dragged by demons on the right; nude female figure on a carriage made of bones on the left; large winged creature vomiting demons on the upper part; rocky landscape with buildings on fire and monstruous creatures; coat of arms at the bottom. 1635 Etching
Bibliographic references: Meaume 1860 / Recherches sur la vie et les ouvrages de Jacques Callot (139.III)
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
Associated with: Louis Phelypeaux de La Vrillière
Acquisition notes: From the Scarisbrick collection of Callot's work: see comment on 1861,0713.1.
